{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
Some f[Am]riends and I in a public house
Were p[G]laying a game of chance one[Am]night
When in[G]to the [F]pub a [E]fireman ran
His [F]face all chalky [E]white.
"What[Am]&rsquo;s up,&rdquo; says Brown, "Have you seen a ghost,
Or have you s[G]een your Aunt [Am]Mariah?"
"Me Aunt Mar[G]iah be b[F]uggered!" says h[E]e,
"The b[F]leedin&rsquo; pub[E]&rsquo;s on fire!"
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
And t[Am]here was Brown, upside down
L[G]appin&rsquo; up the whiskey from [Am]the floor
[G]"Booze, booze!" The [F]firemen [E]cried
As t[F]hey came knockin&rsquo; a[E]t the door (clap clap)
Oh do[Am]n&rsquo;t let &lsquo;em in till it&rsquo;s all drunk up
And s[G]omebody shouted [Am]Maclntyre! MACINTYRE!
And we [G]all got blu[F]e-blind p[E]aralytic drunk
When the [F]Old Dun [E]Cow caught [Am]fire.
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
"[Am]Fire," says Brown, "What a bit of luck.
[G]Everybody follow[Am]me
We&rsquo;[G]ll go down t[F]o the cellar, i[E]f the fire&rsquo;s not there
Then we&rsq[F]uo;ll have a gran[E]d old spree."
So we[Am]went on down after good old Brown
For booz[G]e we could not [Am]miss
And we [G]hadn&rsquo;t[F] been there[E]five minutes before
[F]We were all quite [E]pissed.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
