Oh do[Am]n&rsquo;t let &lsquo;em in till it&rsquo;s all drunk up
And s[G]omebody shouted [Am]Maclntyre! MACINTYRE!
And we [G]all got blu[F]e-blind p[E]aralytic drunk
When the [F]Old Dun [E]Cow caught [Am]fire.
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Then, [Am]Smith walked over to the port wine tub
And [G]gave it just a few hard k[Am]nocks (clap clap)
He st[G]arted t[F]akin&rsquo; of[E]f his pantaloons
Likew[F]ise his shoes and [E]socks
"Hold[Am]on, "says Brown, "that ain&rsquo;t allowed
Ye [G]canna do that in [Am]here
Don&rsquo[G];t go wa[F]shin&rsquo; trot[E]ters in the port wine tub
When we [F]got some low carb [E]beer.
{end_of_verse}

