When the [F]Old Dun [E]Cow caught [Am]fire.
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
And t[Am]hen there came to the old back door
The [G]Vicar of our local [Am]church
And when [G]he had [F]seen our [E]drunken ways
He be[F]gan to scream and [E]curse
"You [Am]drunken sods, you heathen clods
You&rsq[G]uo;ve taken to a dr[Am]unken spree!
And you [G]drank up [F]all that [E]Benedictine Brandy
And you [F]didn&rsquo;t save a dro[E]p for me!"
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
