When the [F]Old Dun [E]Cow caught [Am]fire.
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
And [Am]then there came a mighty crash
Ha[G]lf the bloody roof gave [Am]way
We were [G]almost [F]drowned in the [E]firemen&rsquo;s hose
But [F]we were gonna [E]stay
So we [Am]got some tacks and some old wet sacks
And we [G]nailed ourselves in[Am]side
And we [G]sat there [F]drinkin&rsquo[E]; the finest rum
&lsquo[F];Till we was b[E]leary-eyed
{end_of_verse}

