{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
L[Am]ater that night when the fire was out
We [G]came up from the cellar [Am]below
Our p[G]ub was b[F]urned, our [E]booze was drunk
And our [F]heads were a-hangin&r[E]squo; low
"Oh lo[Am]ok,&rdquo; says Brown, with a look quite queer
It seemed [G]something caught his [Am]ire
"We&rsq[G]uo;ve gott[F]a get dow[E]n to Murphy&rsquo;s pub
It [F]closes on the [E]hour!"
{end_of_verse}

